<br>
Is this also the case on the other PK servers (Tallon, Vallon &amp; Rallos)?<br>
<br>
If NOT, then will &quot;Ice&quot; be the DD of choice for druids at 49 on Sullon, due to the debuff giving the spell a much higher likelihood of landing (even though all the Velious hunters will have high cold resists)?  <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uarlis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arlis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/17/01 4:43:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Fire&quot; and &quot;Ice&quot; on Sullon</span><hr size=1> The 50% debuff increase is supposed to apply to all PvP.<br>
<br>
My personal opinion is that this is rather harsh punishment for all those melee (and non-melee) players that worked hard through many levels to acquire enough resist gear to put up a good fight against casters who have pets, can debuff, can shadow step, gate, sow, snare, are at 70 to 80% effectiveness naked, etc. I play a lot more casters classes than melee classes and it seems a bit unfair to me. I can imagine how most of the melee types feel. <p>Arlis
Wood Elf Druid<BR>
Trillin
Dark Elf Necromancer<BR>
Mault
Halfling Cleric<BR>
Chens
Iksar Monk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaeelebpdm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AeelebPDM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Tactician<br>PvP Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/17/01 9:41:01 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.m-m-s.com/aggressors/images/aeelebbox.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;Fire&quot; and &quot;Ice&quot; on Sullon</span><hr size=1> Fire and Ice are pretty useless against players once they get resists. <br>
<br>
fire is too inefficient to use on one person, and really doesn't do much damage if it lands. <br>
<br>
both of them are pretty easy to resist because they have a double resist check - magic for the debuff portion, and fire/cold for the damage. that is why ice is an all/nothing spell. <br>
<br>
don't forget that both of the debuff portions of those spells don't last very long for you to make much use of them, either.<br>
<br>
Ro's fiery sundering is an excellent spell if you want to debuff FR and nuke away. Ro's is especially deadly to mages, because not only does it drop their DS (30fr) but it debuffs them another 60. <p>--------- Aeeleb Treelover, the Tactician<br>
